  "text": "The Kafka consumer offset commit flow traces from the client-side commitSync() call through the broker's group coordinator to the __consumer_offsets topic. Here is the complete chain:\n\n1. **Client-Side Entry Point**: KafkaConsumer.commitSync() (line 940) is the public API entry point that delegates to the internal delegate.\n\n2. **Internal Consumer Delegate**: AsyncKafkaConsumer.commitSync() (line 879) handles the actual synchronous commit logic by calling commitOffsetsSync() with the offsets to commit.\n\n3. **Coordinator Communication**: ConsumerCoordinator.commitOffsetsSync() (line 1140) orchestrates the offset commit. It calls sendOffsetCommitRequest() (line 1270) to construct and send an OffsetCommitRequest to the group coordinator broker.\n\n4. **Server-Side Request Handler**: KafkaApis.handleOffsetCommitRequest() (line 272 in KafkaApis.scala) receives the request on the broker, performs authorization and metadata validation, then delegates to groupCoordinator.commitOffsets() (line 347).\n\n5. **Group Coordinator Service**: GroupCoordinatorService.commitOffsets() (line 1971) schedules a write operation via runtime.scheduleWriteOperation(), invoking GroupCoordinatorShard.commitOffset().\n\n6. **Coordinator Shard Processing**: GroupCoordinatorShard.commitOffset() (line 852) delegates to OffsetMetadataManager.commitOffset() to process the commit request.\n\n7. **Offset Metadata Management**: OffsetMetadataManager.commitOffset() (line 600) validates the offset commit and creates CoordinatorRecord objects using GroupCoordinatorRecordHelpers.newOffsetCommitRecord(). These records represent the offset commit entries that will be persisted.\n\n8. **Record Batching and Buffering**: CoordinatorRuntime.append() (line 948) appends the CoordinatorRecord objects to an in-memory batch buffer. When the batch is full, exceeds the linger timeout, or becomes transactional, flushCurrentBatch() (line 779) is called.\n\n9. **Partition Write Operation**: CoordinatorRuntime.flushCurrentBatch() calls partitionWriter.append() (line 795) with the serialized records to write them to the log.\n\n10. **Log Append Implementation**: CoordinatorPartitionWriter.append() (line 137 in CoordinatorPartitionWriter.scala) calls replicaManager.appendRecordsToLeader() (line 144) with AppendOrigin.COORDINATOR and the __consumer_offsets topic partition.\n\n11. **Log Storage**: ReplicaManager.appendRecordsToLeader() (line 627 in ReplicaManager.scala) appends the records to the UnifiedLog instance for the __consumer_offsets partition, returning the assigned offset. The records are then written to disk as part of Kafka's log storage subsystem.\n\nThe complete flow ensures that consumer offset commits are durably written to the replicated __consumer_offsets compacted topic, allowing consumer groups to resume consumption from their last committed positions."
}

